6: What, oh what am I to do?
10:
Stop with the drama.
I'm not asking you what's wrong.
19:
I mean, I thought we were doing pretty
good. We've been getting a steady
stream of jobs from the Guild, and I
found some cheap shops in Palpebra.
22:
Okay, let's just get two things straight.
You're TELLING me, and I DIDN'T ASK.
36:
Then you haven't seen HER.
She's HUGE!
How much do you think she eats?!
39:
Actually, what even does she eat?
What am I supposed to do if she lives
off of fairy dust potage? I don't know
how to make that...
50:
And if YOU can't rustle up the food for
her, just get her to help.
58:
Stop being such a baby, and TALK TO
HER.
62:
Hahaha. You were making much ado
about nothing.
69: The Ancients do not need to eat.
76:
We draw energy from the elements
that fill the world.
78:
And even if we were deprived of these,
we would not perish, but fall into
a deep slumber.
85:
Well, that settles it.
Dragon food will NOT be an issue.
89:
Yes... But though I NEED not eat,
that does not mean I CAN not.
And I would very much like to try
some of your famous cooking, Alk.
93:
Happy to oblige, but uh...
What should I make?
96: Anything. I can eat all that you do.
98:
But perhaps, as Nimbus said, it would
be best if I supplied my own food.
114:
I taste herbs and mushrooms from
the World of Evergreen...
An excellent combination.
126:
Because we Ancients did not eat,
we also did not cook. I consider the
culinary arts to be one of mortality's
finest inventions.
130:
What's with the scowl, Alk?
We LIKE the food.
134: Oh, no... I was just thinking...
136:
What if we brought Rams to Oceanus?
Can you imagine all the fish
we'd catch?
140:
I'd never have to worry about keeping
Starview fed again!
145: Alk, a dragon is no fishing trawl.
150:
It's all right, Light.
I enjoy such peaceful pursuits.
156: Wait. So you'll go to Oceanus with me?
160: Haha. Of course. It's a promise.
168:
Truly.
What a wonderful place to live in...
